      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:11:2",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) أَيْنَ يُضْرَبُ الَّذِي يَأْتِي ذَاتَ مَحْرَمٍ بِالسَّيْفِ أَيْنَ هَذِهِ الضَّرْبَةُ قَالَ يُضْرَبُ عُنُقُهُ أَوْ قَالَ تُضْرَبُ رَقَبَتُهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al Hassan, from Ali Bin Asbaat, from Al Hakaam Bin Muskeyn, form Jameel Bin Darraj who said, ",
          "‘I said to Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, ‘Where would he be struck with the sword, the one who came to his <span class=\"iTxt\">Mahram</span> (committed incest), where is this strike to be?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘His neck would be struck’, or said: ‘His throat should be struck’."
        ]
      }
    }
